<div id="pf3620" class="pf w65 h236" data-page-no="3620"><div class="pc pc3620 w65 h236"><div class="t m9a9 xcd h32 y2971 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 11 </div><div class="t m568 x62 h3b y2986 ff6 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">September 11, 1971 </div><div class="t m21cd x38 h11c y1075 ff3 fs22 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE MINISTRY OF MISSIONS 11 </div><div class="t m24a9 x92 h13 y1610 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;But ye are a chosen generation, a royal priesthood, an holy nation, a peculiar </div><div class="t m2377 xc3 h13 ydb8 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">people; that ye should show forth the praises of Him who hath called you out of </div><div class="t mc94 xc3 h13 y202b ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">darkness into His marvelous light.&quot; 1 Peter 2:9. </div><div class="t m4db x3 h4 yc09 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Peter wrote this to his generation. If you </div><div class="t m14c4 xc3 h4 yde3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">had your choice, when would you choose to </div><div class="t m7bb xc3 h4 y9c0 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">live, then or now? Peter could think of his </div><div class="t m22d xc3 h4 ybdd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">generation in the context of Pentecost, when </div><div class="t m2e8 xd3 h4 y102f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;more were converted by one sermon on </div><div class="t m286 xc3 h4 yf4d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the day of Pentecost than were converted </div><div class="t m3a7 xc3 h4 ycdd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">during all the years of Christ&apos;s ministry.&quot;—</div><div class="t mb1e xc3 h4 yd14 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ellen G. White Comments, </div><div class="t mb2 x40 h30 yd14 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SDA Bible Com-</div><div class="t m593 xc3 h30 y9c3 ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mentary, </div><div class="t m5a2 x74 h4 y9c3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Vol. 6, p. 1055. </div><div class="t m816 x3 h4 y1224 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">But let us rather think of &quot;our&quot; genera-</div><div class="t ma73 xc3 h4 y123a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tion: </div><div class="t m988 x3 h4 yf83 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m497 x11 h4 yf83 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A chosen generation—to complete the </div><div class="t m2be x11 h4 yce3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">work committed to the church. </div><div class="t m127 x3 h4 y13a2 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m5af x11 h4 yffd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A royal priesthood—with all, including </div><div class="t mb15 x11 h4 y93f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the laity, sharing in the witness. </div><div class="t m2b6 x3 h4 ya9e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t ma8a x11 h4 ye56 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An holy nation—citizens of God&apos;s </div><div class="t m97 xb4 h4 ybe5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">kingdom, pilgrims and strangers here. </div><div class="t ma2 x3 h4 y8c7 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m224 x17 h4 y1200 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A peculiar people—that is, a select or </div><div class="t m268 xb4 h4 y1226 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">a special people, God&apos;s prized possession. </div><div class="t m36d xa3 h13 yd41 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON OUTLINE </div><div class="t m7a0 x7 h13 y120f ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m121b x9f h13 y120f ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Church Compared to the Body </div><div class="t m6b0 x9f h13 y90d ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 Cor. 12:12-14 </div><div class="t mec2 x7 h13 yae5 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m54d x9f h13 yae5 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Our Relationship to the Church </div><div class="t m8f8 x9f h13 y1030 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and to Christ </div><div class="t m1324 x9f h13 y939 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mark 3:32-35 </div><div class="t m2ca x7 h13 y9fb ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1728 x9f h13 y9fb ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Purpose of Leadership </div><div class="t m1002 x9f h13 y5a9 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eph. 4:11-14 </div><div class="t mb90 x7 h13 y9c6 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t mad8 x9